1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 28-01 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to service of summons and time limitations for serving an answer to a
3 claim.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 28-01 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 Service of summons - Answer - Time limitation.
8 1. A summons in a civil action served on an individual within the state must include a
9 reference to a legal self-help program administered by the supreme court.
10 2. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, a defendant shall serve an answer to the
11 complaint or to a cross-claim, or a reply to a counterclaim, within thirty days after
12 service upon the pleading in which the claim is asserted.
